{{Lunisolar November}} 
'''November 29''' is the 29th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)}}  – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} . If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小}}  then this is the last day; if {{Nihongo|Big|大}}  then it is the second-last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜}} is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負}}.
== Events ==
* {{ill|Tengen (Japan)|ja|天元 (日本)|lt=Tengen|lt_ja=天元}}  first year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|978|ja|978th year}} {{ill|December 31|ja|12月31日}} ) – Because the following year was struck by the misfortune of Yōgo, the era name was changed from {{ill|Jōgen (Japan)|ja|貞元 (日本)|lt=Jōgen|lt_ja=貞元}}  to {{ill|era change|ja|改元}} 
* {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治}}  first year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}} {{ill|1185|ja|1185th year}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日}} ) – The Kamakura Shogunate, under the pretext of pursuing {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経}} , obtained imperial authorization from {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|lt=Go-Shirakawa Hōō|lt_ja=後白河法皇}}  to station {{ill|shugo|ja|守護}}  and {{ill|jitō|ja|地頭}}  throughout the provinces.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano}}  {{ill|1546|ja|1546}}  {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日}} ) – {{ill|Kuroda Takahisa|ja|黒田孝高}} , a military commander († {{ill|1604|ja|1604}} ).
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦}}  {{ill|1871|ja|1871}}  {{ill|January 19|ja|1月19日}} ) – {{ill|Koganei Kimiko|ja|小金井喜美子}} , a novelist, essayist, and younger sister of {{ill|Mori Ōgai|ja|森鷗外}}  († {{ill|1956|ja|1956}} ).

== Deaths ==
