'''November 29''' is the 29th day of month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}}  – the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} . If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}}  then this is the last day; if {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}}  then it is the second-last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} is {{ill|Senbu|ja|先負|qq=}}.
== Events ==
* {{ill|Tengen (Japan)|ja|天元 (日本)|lt=Tengen|lt_ja=天元|qq=}}  first year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|978|ja|978th year|qq=}} {{ill|December 31|ja|12月31日|qq=}} ) – Because the following year was struck by the misfortune of Yōgo, the era name was changed from {{ill|Jōgen (Japan)|ja|貞元 (日本)|lt=Jōgen|lt_ja=貞元|qq=}}  to {{ill|era change|ja|改元|qq=}} 
* {{ill|Bunji|ja|文治|qq=}}  first year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}} {{ill|1185|ja|1185th year|qq=}} {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=}} ) – The Kamakura Shogunate, under the pretext of pursuing {{ill|Minamoto no Yoshitsune|ja|源義経|qq=}} , obtained imperial authorization from {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|lt=Go-Shirakawa Hōō|lt_ja=後白河法皇|qq=}}  to station {{ill|shugo|ja|守護|qq=}}  and {{ill|jitō|ja|地頭|qq=}}  throughout the provinces.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=}} 15th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}}  {{ill|1546|ja|1546|qq=}}  {{ill|December 22|ja|12月22日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Kuroda Takahisa|ja|黒田孝高|qq=}} , a military commander († {{ill|1604|ja|1604|qq=}} ).
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=}}  {{ill|1871|ja|1871|qq=}}  {{ill|January 19|ja|1月19日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Koganei Kimiko|ja|小金井喜美子|qq=}} , a novelist, essayist, and younger sister of {{ill|Mori Ōgai|ja|森鷗外|qq=}}  († {{ill|1956|ja|1956|qq=}} ).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|Hōreki|qq=}} 7th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=}}  {{ill|1758|ja|1758|qq=}}  {{ill|January 9|ja|1月9日|qq=}} ) – {{ill|Kurushima Yoshinobu|ja|久留島喜内|qq=}} , a wasan expert (* {{ill|1660|ja|1660|qq=}}  circa).

