[[:en:Jōgen (Heian period)|Jōgen]] to {{ill|era change|ja|改元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/era change|qq=}} * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunji]] first year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – The Kamakura Shogunate, under the pretext of pursuing [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshitsune|Minamoto no Yoshitsune]] , obtained imperial authorization from {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|ja|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|lt=Go-Shirakawa Hōō|lt_ja=後白河法皇|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} to station [[:en:Shugo|shugo]] and [[:en:Jitō|jitō]] throughout the provinces. == Births == * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon (era)|qq=}} 15th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1546|1546]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – [[:en:Kuroda Yoshitaka|Kuroda Takahisa]] , a military commander († [[:en:1604|1604]] ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] {{ill|1871|ja|1871|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} [[:en:January 19|January 19]] ) – {{ill|Koganei Kimiko|ja|小金井喜美子|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koganei Kimiko|qq=}} , a novelist, essayist, and younger sister of [[:en:Mori Ōgai|Mori Ōgai]] († {{ill|1956|ja|1956|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1956|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1000}} ).
== Deaths == * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 7th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] {{ill|1758|ja|1758|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1758|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} [[:en:January 9|January 9]] ) – {{ill|Kurushima Yoshinobu|ja|久留島喜内|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kurushima Yoshinobu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 久留島義太}} , a wasan expert (* {{ill|1660|ja|1660|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1660|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} circa).
