kidata|WD=Q9418169}}{{efn|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senbu|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9418169}}. == Events == * [[:en:Tengen (era)|Tengen]] first year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:978|978]] [[:en:December 31|December 31]] ) – Because the following year was struck by the misfortune of Yōgo, the era name was changed from [[:en:Jōgen (Heian period)|Jōgen]] to {{ill|era change|ja|改元|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/era change|qq=|1=era change|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11498853}} * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunji]] first year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – The Kamakura Shogunate, under the pretext of pursuing [[:en:Minamoto no Yoshitsune|Minamoto no Yoshitsune]] , obtained imperial authorization from {{ill|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|1=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|2=ja|3=後白河天皇|qid=Q317984|ja|Emperor Go-Shirakawa|1=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|2=ja|3=後白河天皇|qid=Q317984|lt=Go-Shirakawa Hōō|lt_ja=後白河法皇|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Go-Shirakawa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} to station [[:en:Shugo|shugo]] and [[:en:Jitō|jitō]] throughout the provinces. == Births == * {{ill|Tenmon (era)|ja|天文|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenmon (era)|qq=|1=Tenbun|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q21096812}} 15th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1546|1546]] [[:en:December 22|December 22]] ) – [[:en:Kuroda Yoshitaka|Kuroda Takahisa]] , a military commander († [[:en:1604|1604]] ). * [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:January 19|January 19]] ) – {{ill|Koganei Kimiko|ja|小金井喜美子|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Koganei Kimiko|qq=|1=Koganei Kimiko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11464316}} , a novelist, essayist, and younger sister of [[:en:Mori Ōgai|Mori Ōgai]] († [[:en:1956|1956]] ).
